<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════
     PROBLEM → SOLUTION
════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<section class="pvh-problem" aria-label="Problem and solution">
  <div class="pvh-problem-inner">
    <div class="pvh-problem-col" data-pvh-enter>
      <span class="pvh-tag">The problem</span>
      <h2 class="pvh-problem-heading">Most fountains are loud, plastic, and built to be hidden.</h2>
      <p class="pvh-problem-body">The ones that work end up under the sink. The ones that look decent don't work well. Either way, you're always aware of it — and so is your cat.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="pvh-problem-col pvh-problem-col--solution" data-pvh-enter style="transition-delay:0.12s">
      <span class="pvh-tag">Why ceramic</span>
      <h2 class="pvh-problem-heading">Ceramic holds water cooler, doesn't leach taste, and wipes clean.</h2>
      <p class="pvh-problem-body">The same material as the plates in your kitchen — completely inert, naturally odour-free. Brook is what we'd leave on the counter and not think twice about. That was the standard we built to.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════
     HOW IT WORKS
════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<section class="pvh-steps" id="pvh-how-it-works" aria-label="How Brook works">
  <div class="pvh-steps-inner">
    <div class="pvh-section-header" data-pvh-enter>
      <span class="pvh-tag">Why it matters</span>
      <h2 class="pvh-section-title">Why cats and still water don't mix.</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="pvh-steps-grid">
      <div class="pvh-step" data-pvh-enter>
        <div class="pvh-step-num">01</div>
        <h3 class="pvh-step-title">Cats distrust still water by instinct</h3>
        <p class="pvh-step-body">Desert-descended animals, cats instinctively avoid water that isn't moving. A still bowl triggers that wariness; a flowing fountain doesn't. It's not a quirk — it's evolution.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="pvh-step" data-pvh-enter style="transition-delay:0.1s">
        <div class="pvh-step-num">02</div>
        <h3 class="pvh-step-title">Most indoor cats drink far less than they should</h3>
        <p class="pvh-step-body">Chronic low-grade dehydration is behind kidney disease, urinary issues, and low energy — all common in cats fed dry food. The gap between "enough to survive" and "enough to thrive" is often just a better water source.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="pvh-step" data-pvh-enter style="transition-delay:0.2s">
        <div class="pvh-step-num">03</div>
        <h3 class="pvh-step-title">Brook removes the friction</h3>
        <p class="pvh-step-body">Running water, triple-stage filtration, near-silent pump. Leave it out. Let it run. Most owners notice their cat drinking more within the first day.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

